{
  "target": "MaximumLikelihood",
  "kind": "model_estimation",
  "source": "Exact oracle values dumped from the REAL RMC.BestFit MaximumLikelihood via tools/oracle_emitter --dump (M14) and reproduced by tools/verify_oracles.py. Exercises the `mixture` model type: EM-seeded defaults + NelderMead; the second case sets zero_inflated: true on data with zeros (the zero weight is pinned to the data's zero-value relative frequency, not estimated). Parameter layout: [w_1, w_2, mu_1, sigma_1, mu_2, sigma_2]. These fits exercise the C# SetParameters(ref) weight-normalization WRITE-BACK into the optimizer's own working vectors (ported in M14 -- see model_base.hpp's MUTABLE-PARAMETER note); the M13 self-computed values predate that fix and differed in the raw weight coordinates (scale-equivalent optimum). NelderMead point values rel 1e-9. Covariance/standard errors are deliberately NOT asserted: the real C# covariance at this optimum is INDEFINITE (negative diagonal entries; GetStandardErrors clamps to 0) with off-diagonals at finite-difference noise scale (~1e-10) -- the M10 near-singular-Hessian ledger finding, confirmed against the real library; asserting noise is meaningless.",
  "datasets": {
    "bimodal_series": [
      520,
      580,
      610,
      650,
      700,
      730,
      760,
      800,
      850,
      880,
      910,
      950,
      990,
      1030,
      1080,
      5000,
      5400,
      5800,
      6300,
      6800
    ],
    "zero_series": [
      0,
      0,
      120,
      340,
      0,
      560,
      780,
      150,
      430,
      920,
      210,
      380,
      0,
      640,
      275
    ]
  },
  "cases": [
    {
      "name": "two_normal_mixture",
      "construct": {
        "model": {
          "type": "mixture",
          "families": [
            "Normal",
            "Normal"
          ],
          "dataset": "bimodal_series"
        },
        "optimizer": "NelderMead"
      },
      "assertions": [
        {
          "method": "parameter",
          "args": [
            0
          ],
          "expected": 0.7499898648904965,
          "mode": "rel",
          "tol": 1e-09
        },
        {
          "method": "parameter",
          "args": [
            1
          ],
          "expected": 0.2500101351095036,
          "mode": "rel",
          "tol": 1e-09
        },
        {
